TRAINEE: It's right in front?

903
00:32:38,368 --> 00:32:39,799
HANBI: I can see the audience really well.

904
00:32:39,799 --> 00:32:40,736
JAEWON: Oh, hi!

905
00:32:42,784 --> 00:32:45,568
(It finally starts to feel real,
thinking about meeting fans up close)

906
00:32:46,048 --> 00:32:46,944
(Emotional)
JUSTIN: Wow, this is...

907
00:32:46,944 --> 00:32:47,840
HYUNJUN: Say hello, say hello.

908
00:32:48,544 --> 00:32:49,856
TRAINEE: Hello.

909
00:32:49,856 --> 00:32:51,040
HYUNJUN: Hello.

910
00:32:51,776 --> 00:32:53,216
HANBI: At a place where we used to hang out...

911
00:32:53,856 --> 00:32:55,899
HANBI: It's amazing to perform here.

912
00:32:56,166 --> 00:32:56,928
HANBI: I remember this.

913
00:32:57,833 --> 00:32:58,944
HANBI: Wow...

914
00:32:59,433 --> 00:33:00,512
(It feels different being back at school)

915
00:33:00,512 --> 00:33:01,632
TRAINEE: It's been a while.

916
00:33:01,632 --> 00:33:03,136
HANBI: That's the waiting room over there.

917
00:33:04,699 --> 00:33:07,936
(SMTR25)

918
00:33:08,576 --> 00:33:09,408
HANBI: The waiting room, the waiting room.

919
00:33:09,856 --> 00:33:11,299
HANBI: Wow, this used to be the music room.

920
00:33:11,299 --> 00:33:12,256
(A spacious waiting room for 15 trainees)

921
00:33:12,272 --> 00:33:13,142
TRAINEE: This is the first time here.

922
00:33:14,176 --> 00:33:16,480
HANBI: Hey, there's even a sofa!

923
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:20,933
HANBI: It's quite spacious probably
because there are so many people.

924
00:33:22,666 --> 00:33:25,399
(Unpacking in the waiting room one by one)

925
00:33:25,568 --> 00:33:27,899
JUSTIN: There are name tags outside.

926
00:33:27,899 --> 00:33:28,736
JUSTIN: You can find and take your name tags.

927
00:33:28,767 --> 00:33:30,208
- TRAINEE: Okay.
- TRAINEE: Okay.

928
00:33:31,133 --> 00:33:32,256
HANBI: Let's grab our name tags.

929
00:33:32,544 --> 00:33:35,533
SONGHA: Shouldn't we be wearing in-ears for this too?

930
00:33:35,533 --> 00:33:37,376
TRAINEE: I guess we should.

931
00:33:37,376 --> 00:33:39,200
TRAINEE: We couldn't hear anything earlier.

932
00:33:39,866 --> 00:33:42,666
(Getting ready for full stage rehearsal)

933
00:33:43,233 --> 00:33:44,999
(They pick up their name tags)

934
00:33:50,333 --> 00:33:53,466
(And in-ears, trying to calm their nerves)

935
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:57,633
STAFF: I'll secure your in-ears with tape.

936
00:34:02,033 --> 00:34:04,366
(They fix them tightly so they won't fall out)

937
00:34:05,466 --> 00:34:08,099
(They also check the mic fit)

938
00:34:08,299 --> 00:34:09,312
SONGHA: Let's go, guys, let's go!

939
00:34:09,312 --> 00:34:11,168
TRAINEE: Guys, let's go to the stage!

940
00:34:11,296 --> 00:34:12,207
TRAINEE: Let's go!

941
00:34:12,699 --> 00:34:14,933
(Off to stage rehearsal!)

942
00:34:18,999 --> 00:34:22,199
(Finally, it's time to stand on stage)

943
00:34:22,912 --> 00:34:24,896
DANIEL: We can do this! Fighting!

944
00:34:25,088 --> 00:34:25,888
TRAINEE: Fighting!

945
00:34:27,072 --> 00:34:28,608
HANBI: Whoa!

946
00:34:28,608 --> 00:34:29,600
(WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL school festival)

947
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:31,168
(Blazing sunlight)

948
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:33,504
(Weather forecast: clear and refreshing)

949
00:34:33,504 --> 00:34:36,384
(What will happen in four hours)

950
00:34:36,933 --> 00:34:39,833
(Didn't expect the show to move this fast, huh?)

951
00:34:40,733 --> 00:34:41,888
HANBI: The weather is so nice.

952
00:34:42,799 --> 00:34:43,872
TRAINEE: Is everyone here?

953
00:34:43,872 --> 00:34:44,992
(Unaware of what's coming)

954
00:34:44,992 --> 00:34:45,536
TRAINEE: Is everyone here?

955
00:34:45,536 --> 00:34:47,733
(The trainees are full of excitement)
TRAINEE: Are the mics working?

956
00:34:48,224 --> 00:34:49,533
HANBI: First off, everyone? Everyone!

957
00:34:49,533 --> 00:34:51,366
(HANBI tries to calm the excited group)
HANBI: Be quiet, quiet, quiet, quiet.

958
00:34:51,648 --> 00:34:53,067
HANBI: Let's greet them first!

959
00:34:53,766 --> 00:34:55,333
(Facing all the staff involved in the performance)
HANBI: We'd like to say hello to everyone. Two, three.

960
00:34:55,699 --> 00:34:57,024
(Greeting)
ALL: Hello!

961
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,848
ALL: Please take good care of us.

962
00:34:59,966 --> 00:35:02,399
(They clap for themselves modestly)

963
00:35:02,399 --> 00:35:03,200
TRAINEE: Let's try it.

964
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:04,192
TRAINEE: Let's do it.

965
00:35:04,192 --> 00:35:06,080
HANBI: Could you play the song for us, please?

966
00:35:07,566 --> 00:35:11,399
(They run through "Into the New World"
for the first time on stage)

967
00:35:13,699 --> 00:35:15,899
(CHARLIE has a flying jump part)

968
00:35:17,792 --> 00:35:18,599
CHARLIE: Hey, oh!

969
00:35:18,599 --> 00:35:20,699
(Not enough space to jump)

970
00:35:23,333 --> 00:35:25,799
(After the first stage rehearsal)

971
00:35:28,366 --> 00:35:29,952
(Decided to adjust CHARLIE's position again!)
SONGHA: We'll just fix CHARLIE's part,

972
00:35:29,952 --> 00:35:31,266
SONGHA: as there isn't enough space.

973
00:35:31,744 --> 00:35:33,899
(Joking)
SONGHA: CHARLIE, want to jump from here?

974
00:35:33,899 --> 00:35:35,499
(Jumping into the audience seats)

975
00:35:35,766 --> 00:35:37,533
(The scary part is, it's actually possible)

976
00:35:37,664 --> 00:35:39,599
(Anyone having any more issues?)
SONGHA: Anyone having any more problems?

977
00:35:39,712 --> 00:35:40,608
(Nope)

978
00:35:40,608 --> 00:35:41,472
SONGHA: None, right?

979
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:44,566
(While the staff reset things)
SONGHA: The set is really cool, kind of really...

980
00:35:44,992 --> 00:35:46,560
SONGHA: It feels like a school festival, doesn't it?

981
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,872
SONGHA: Like they spent a lot of money!

982
00:35:47,872 --> 00:35:50,466
SONGHA: It feels more like a college festival.

983
00:35:50,466 --> 00:35:51,520
JUSTIN: Hey! Hey!

984
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,248
KASSHO: Hey!

985
00:35:53,599 --> 00:35:55,199
SONGHA: Isn't that totally OH HYUNJUN?

986
00:35:55,399 --> 00:35:56,866
(HYUNJUN's tone)

987
00:35:57,199 --> 00:35:58,999
(Perfectly imitated)

988
00:35:59,264 --> 00:36:00,672
JUSTIN: There's no 'Hoi'?

989
00:36:01,799 --> 00:36:03,733
(What they mean by "hoi" is...)

990
00:36:04,166 --> 00:36:04,576
(A sound that habitually comes from CHARLIE's part)

991
00:36:04,576 --> 00:36:06,880
TRAINEE: Hoi, hoi, hoi, hoi.

992
00:36:07,199 --> 00:36:08,999
(They say "hoi" more than Dooly)

993
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,624
JUSTIN: Here's "Hoi".

994
00:36:11,136 --> 00:36:12,736
(Hoi...!)
TRAINEE: There's no "Hoi", "Hoi"!

995
00:36:12,736 --> 00:36:14,688
SONGHA: Or later, we could go up there

996
00:36:14,688 --> 00:36:15,776
SONGHA: and write "hoi" with a marker.

997
00:36:15,776 --> 00:36:17,088
- KASSHO: Hoi, hoi.
- JUSTIN: Hoi, hoi.

998
00:36:17,599 --> 00:36:20,133
(Too many "hoi"s could be a problem)
TRAINEE: Hoi, hoi, hoi.

999
00:36:20,566 --> 00:36:21,312
(Next, rehearsal for Class A.U.I, Year 90)

1000
00:36:21,312 --> 00:36:22,399
JUSTIN: We'll get it done.

1001
00:36:22,399 --> 00:36:23,166
HYUNJUN: Let's do it.

1002
00:36:23,166 --> 00:36:24,320
- TRAINEE: We can do it.
- TRAINEE: Fighting!

1003
00:36:25,033 --> 00:36:28,133
(Class '90, "You, In the Fantasy" stage rehearsal begins!)

1004
00:36:28,544 --> 00:36:30,399
SADAHARU: It really feels like a school festival.

1005
00:36:30,833 --> 00:36:31,712
(Enjoying, wholesome bottled water)
HANBI: Feels like a school festival.

1006
00:36:31,712 --> 00:36:32,416
SADAHARU: Feels like a school festival.

1007
00:36:32,416 --> 00:36:34,799
HANBI: Being at school like this...

1008
00:36:34,799 --> 00:36:36,699
HANBI: It really feels like a school festival.

1009
00:36:37,166 --> 00:36:38,464
HANBI: With friends right in front of us!

1010
00:36:38,464 --> 00:36:39,366
HANBI: Our alumni are here.

1011
00:36:39,366 --> 00:36:41,233
(Group of alumni)
TRAINEE: Wow, at school...

1012
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,712
HANBI: It really feels like a school festival.

1013
00:36:43,712 --> 00:36:44,672
HANBI: It's a strange feeling.

1014
00:36:45,199 --> 00:36:46,933
HANBI: I've never actually
performed at a school festival.

1015
00:36:49,433 --> 00:36:51,799
(First rehearsal finished)

1016
00:36:52,366 --> 00:36:54,999
(Heavy breathing fills the microphones)

1017
00:36:55,699 --> 00:36:58,533
NICHOLAS: Let's line up once when we stand in a row.

1018
00:36:58,733 --> 00:37:00,133
JUSTIN: Energy!

1019
00:37:00,133 --> 00:37:01,888
HYUNJUN: It's all about energy!

1020
00:37:02,799 --> 00:37:04,036
HYUNJUN: Energy!

1021
00:37:04,036 --> 00:37:05,056
(Their voices blast through the in-ears)

1022
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:06,560
HANBI: It's all about energy, energy.

1023
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:06,912
(He responds back)

1024
00:37:07,232 --> 00:37:08,384
DANIEL: Energy!

1025
00:37:08,384 --> 00:37:09,248
(Catchphrase)

1026
00:37:09,833 --> 00:37:12,199
(The rehearsal for Class '90 resumes)

1027
00:37:12,366 --> 00:37:15,599
(Monitoring friends' performances)

1028
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:16,736
KASSHO: Let's do it one more time!

1029
00:37:16,736 --> 00:37:18,366
JUSTIN: Just the positions!

1030
00:37:18,699 --> 00:37:19,999
JUSTIN: Just one more time!

1031
00:37:20,566 --> 00:37:22,933
(Rehearse once more)

1032
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:25,120
(Meanwhile, the audience has grown)

1033
00:37:27,466 --> 00:37:29,056
(Under HAMIN's watch)

1034
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:30,176
SONGHA: Fighting!

1035
00:37:30,176 --> 00:37:31,533
(Rat-a-tat-tat)

1036
00:37:31,533 --> 00:37:33,266
(A clumsy but kind older brother)

1037
00:37:33,472 --> 00:37:34,304
(It's still party time here)
TRAINEE: You are

1038
00:37:35,424 --> 00:37:36,448
TRAINEE: in the fantasy.

1039
00:37:36,833 --> 00:37:38,899
(Song ends)
(Disperse)

1040
00:37:39,584 --> 00:37:40,032
(Class '90 A.U.I's "You, In the Fantasy"
stage rehearsal ends)

1041
00:37:40,032 --> 00:37:40,736
TRAINEE: Are you okay?

1042
00:37:40,736 --> 00:37:41,600
TRAINEE: No issues, right?

1043
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:42,368
TRAINEE: None.

1044
00:37:42,766 --> 00:37:45,466
(KASSHO is completely worn out)

1045
00:37:45,824 --> 00:37:48,096
NICHOLAS: Water... is there any?

1046
00:37:48,096 --> 00:37:50,699
(Cries for survival everywhere)
TRAINEE: Is there any tissue?

1047
00:37:50,933 --> 00:37:52,666
(Outdoor performance)
KASSHO: It's harder when it's outside.

1048
00:37:53,024 --> 00:37:54,927
KASSHO: Wow, even just marking positions is exhausting.

1049
00:37:55,552 --> 00:37:57,472
(Checking KASSHO's condition)

1050
00:37:57,824 --> 00:37:58,880
HAMIN: Wow, you've gotten old, huh?

1051
00:37:59,744 --> 00:38:01,248
HAMIN: You aged after dancing twice!

1052
00:38:01,666 --> 00:38:03,199
(Rapid aging)

1053
00:38:03,433 --> 00:38:04,096
JUSTIN: Ah, this is...

1054
00:38:04,096 --> 00:38:05,120
(Immediate diagnosis)
HYUNJUN: Your stomach hurts, right?

1055
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,766
JUSTIN: It's because I'm too full.

1056
00:38:06,766 --> 00:38:08,320
WOOLIN: I'm hurting here...

1057
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:09,399
(Zombie)
JUSTIN: I can't breathe.

1058
00:38:09,399 --> 00:38:11,033
HYUNJUN: I've got a bit of a feeling
like I need the restroom.

1059
00:38:11,033 --> 00:38:12,599
(STAFF:?)

1060
00:38:12,599 --> 00:38:14,333
STAFF: You can go to the restroom.

1061
00:38:14,333 --> 00:38:16,096
HYUNJUN: No, it just feels like it...

1062
00:38:16,096 --> 00:38:17,333
HYUNJUN: It's like it's coming out here...

1063
00:38:17,333 --> 00:38:18,866
TRAINEE: Let's go!

1064
00:38:19,133 --> 00:38:20,666
("Love And Remember" stage rehearsal)
SONGHA: Yes, we'll try "Love And Remember".

1065
00:38:23,899 --> 00:38:26,399
(This time, DANIEL is watching)

1066
00:38:26,944 --> 00:38:32,000
(If you guys weren't here, our class would be first...)
(It's just the editing)

1067
00:38:32,384 --> 00:38:33,568
HANBI: You need to move further back there.

1068
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:36,032
(Issues noticed during practice)
HANBI: And KACHIN, you should pull that back.

1069
00:38:36,032 --> 00:38:37,056
- KACHIN: Ah, yes yes!
- HANBI: Yes, there.

1070
00:38:37,056 --> 00:38:37,952
(They adjust things one by one)

1071
00:38:37,952 --> 00:38:39,072
HANBI: Where is it, there...

1072
00:38:39,552 --> 00:38:41,120
(Totally exposed)

1073
00:38:41,599 --> 00:38:42,496
(Forehead forcibly exposed by the strong wind)

1074
00:38:42,496 --> 00:38:43,520
SONGHA: Ah, my hair seriously...

1075
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:46,816
KACHIN: When I sing "I love you,"
my hair keeps messing up like this.

1076
00:38:46,816 --> 00:38:48,768
HANBI: Mine does that too.
It turns into perilla-leaf hair.

1077
00:38:49,733 --> 00:38:52,833
(Wind-grown organic perilla leaves)

1078
00:38:53,266 --> 00:38:55,199
(Perilla leaves appear)

1079
00:38:55,766 --> 00:38:58,099
(Another perilla leaf)

1080
00:38:58,499 --> 00:39:01,333
(Perilla leaves are dicot plants)

1081
00:39:02,066 --> 00:39:03,766
(Perilla leaves gone)

1082
00:39:04,566 --> 00:39:07,233
(New perilla leaf arrives)

1083
00:39:07,296 --> 00:39:09,024
- TRAINEE: Thank you.
- TRAINEE: Thank you.

1084
00:39:09,024 --> 00:39:10,304
(Practice ends, the "perilla leaves" disperse)

1085
00:39:10,933 --> 00:39:13,533
(SONGHA elegantly wipes off sweat)

1086
00:39:13,599 --> 00:39:15,499
(What about enthusiastic KACHIN?)

1087
00:39:15,968 --> 00:39:17,472
(Full sauna mode)

1088
00:39:17,472 --> 00:39:18,464
SADAHARU: Did you shower?

1089
00:39:18,464 --> 00:39:18,976
KACHIN: Yeah!

1090
00:39:20,033 --> 00:39:20,960
KACHIN: I'm the only one sweating.

1091
00:39:22,999 --> 00:39:25,133
(Class '10, "CALL ME BABY" stage rehearsal)

1092
00:39:25,133 --> 00:39:27,599
(For now, focus on the formation)
DANIEL: Let's focus on the formation.

1093
00:39:27,744 --> 00:39:28,766
DANIEL: And go hard!

1094
00:39:29,399 --> 00:39:31,424
- HAMIN: Right from the start?
- DANIEL: Yes, go hard right away

1095
00:39:32,199 --> 00:39:34,033
(Dancing hard)

1096
00:39:34,499 --> 00:39:36,799
(Professional monitoring agent SONGHA)

1097
00:39:37,199 --> 00:39:38,899
(Tenant moved in upstairs)

1098
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,952
(If only that class wasn't here...)

1099
00:39:42,016 --> 00:39:43,235
(Mid-point check)
DANIEL: With pace and slow.

1100
00:39:44,256 --> 00:39:45,888
DANIEL: Match the moves precisely!

1101
00:39:45,888 --> 00:39:47,533
DANIEL: Don't lose energy here.

1102
00:39:47,584 --> 00:39:49,024
DANIEL: Let's take a short break.

1103
00:39:49,024 --> 00:39:50,112
DANIEL: Then go hard again.

1104
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:53,216
DANIEL: Just 30 seconds.

1105
00:39:53,504 --> 00:39:55,667
(What you can do in 30 seconds)
TRAINEE: Because of the dust.

1106
00:39:59,466 --> 00:39:59,776
SONGHA: Oh.

1107
00:39:59,776 --> 00:40:01,920
SONGHA: DANIEL drank mine.

1108
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,072
(Drinking mineral water with a straw)
TRAINEE: Oh, SUNGHYUN.

1109
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:05,536
(Spurt!!)
TRAINEE: Oh dear.

1110
00:40:05,696 --> 00:40:07,456
(Spraying more than drinking)
SONGHA: SUNGHYUN, what are you doing?

1111
00:40:07,766 --> 00:40:09,833
(Accidentally turned into a water dispenser)

1112
00:40:10,176 --> 00:40:11,360
SONGHA: It's too hot, right? Because of the sunshine...

1113
00:40:11,978 --> 00:40:13,344
HARUTA: It's way too hot.

1114
00:40:14,666 --> 00:40:15,360
(After the rehearsal ends,
Class '90 heads to the waiting room!)

1115
00:40:15,383 --> 00:40:17,504
TRAINEE: Can I still pull it out?

1116
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:19,232
NICHOLAS: Wow.

1117
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:22,848
KASSHO: Wow, my legs feel so heavy.

1118
00:40:23,505 --> 00:40:28,736
JUSTIN: We need to manage our stamina well.
If we're out of breath from the start, we're dead!

1119
00:40:29,472 --> 00:40:31,133
JUSTIN: We have another rehearsal later.

1120
00:40:31,133 --> 00:40:32,960
JUSTIN: Let's go harder then.

1121
00:40:33,088 --> 00:40:34,566
(Camera rehearsal in the evening)
JUSTIN: Yeah, camera rehearsal.

1122
00:40:34,566 --> 00:40:36,766
TRAINEE: We have to go hard
during the camera rehearsal anyway.

1123
00:40:37,102 --> 00:40:38,609
TRAINEE: Might as well do it then.

1124
00:40:39,666 --> 00:40:41,600
(Cold bottled water is a good device
to take out the heat)

1125
00:40:41,664 --> 00:40:44,899
HYUNJUN: I don't think I can focus
if I see my older sister.

1126
00:40:45,024 --> 00:40:46,048
(HYUNJUN's older sister even applied)
KASSHO: Is she really coming?

1127
00:40:46,098 --> 00:40:47,648
(and got selected as an audience)
HYUNJUN: Yeah, she really is.

1128
00:40:47,810 --> 00:40:50,112
(On stage)
NICHOLAS: Talk about your sister if you want!

1129
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:51,328
JUSTIN: Ms. Big Sister.

1130
00:40:51,392 --> 00:40:52,608
JUSTIN: Please give a big round of applause.

1131
00:40:52,864 --> 00:40:54,304
(Perfect way to embarrass his sister)

1132
00:40:54,432 --> 00:40:56,733
(Expected reaction from his sister)HYUNJUN: That's not the HYUNJUN
who was lounging at home, right?

1133
00:40:56,896 --> 00:40:58,240
HYUNJUN: What do you think of HYUNJUN you saw on stage?

1134
00:40:58,300 --> 00:40:59,296
JUSTIN: Oh, that's nice!

1135
00:40:59,666 --> 00:41:01,166
(What????)

1136
00:41:01,166 --> 00:41:03,499
(Was she impressed by the lounging HYUNJUN?)
JUSTIN: That's actually kind of really touching.

1137
00:41:03,499 --> 00:41:04,416
HYUNJUN: You think it's touching?

1138
00:41:04,416 --> 00:41:06,633
JUSTIN: I mean, you showed
a cool side of yourself on stage.

1139
00:41:06,633 --> 00:41:08,666
(Understood?)

1140
00:41:08,768 --> 00:41:10,666
HYUNJUN: My older sister is a fan of DANIEL.

1141
00:41:10,666 --> 00:41:12,099
HYUNJUN: She really likes him.

1142
00:41:12,566 --> 00:41:13,120
(HYUNJUN's older sister's favorite)

1143
00:41:13,139 --> 00:41:13,728
HYUNJUN: For real.

1144
00:41:14,432 --> 00:41:16,096
HYUNJUN: She really likes DANIEL.

1145
00:41:16,594 --> 00:41:17,376
HYUNJUN: She also likes you, KASSHO.

1146
00:41:17,376 --> 00:41:17,856
KASSHO: Really?

1147
00:41:17,856 --> 00:41:18,560
(Bias)
HYUNJUN: But...

1148
00:41:19,264 --> 00:41:20,416
HYUNJUN: My sister has her picks!

1149
00:41:20,582 --> 00:41:20,928
KASSHO: Still...

1150
00:41:21,088 --> 00:41:22,366
(Favorite DANIEL)
HYUNJUN: DANIEL.

1151
00:41:22,366 --> 00:41:23,168
(Second favorite KASSHO)
HYUNJUN: KASSHO.

1152
00:41:23,232 --> 00:41:24,128
(Grin)

1153
00:41:28,544 --> 00:41:29,152
JUSTIN: That's it?

1154
00:41:29,184 --> 00:41:30,566
HYUNJUN: Oh, but SONGHA...

1155
00:41:31,166 --> 00:41:34,066
(It's clear that the younger brother isn't on the favorite list)
HYUNJUN: Everyone seems to like him.

1156
00:41:34,368 --> 00:41:37,699
(Stage rehearsal finished)
ALL: Thank you!

1157
00:41:38,433 --> 00:41:39,566
DANIEL: Hehehe.

1158
00:41:40,433 --> 00:41:41,760
(Somehow DANIEL seems excited)

1159
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:45,664
DANIEL: You're in the fantasy.

1160
00:41:46,688 --> 00:41:47,520
SONGHA: Come here.

1161
00:41:48,928 --> 00:41:52,416
DANIEL: What am I, a puppy? Just go like that?

1162
00:41:52,539 --> 00:41:53,440
SONGHA: You're going to do it, aren't you?
Then okay, I got it...

1163
00:41:53,766 --> 00:41:55,466
(Correct)

1164
00:41:55,466 --> 00:41:56,448
STAFF: The writer is calling you.

1165
00:41:56,448 --> 00:41:56,896
DANIEL: Yes.

1166
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:02,500
(DANIELsuddenly smiles and heads somewhere)

1167
00:42:03,066 --> 00:42:05,833
(He goes into the waiting tent)

1168
00:42:06,666 --> 00:42:08,608
DANIEL: Hehehehehe.

1169
00:42:08,736 --> 00:42:10,633
DANIEL: Just wait, HANBI!

1170
00:42:11,066 --> 00:42:13,833
(They prepare a surprise party for HANBI,
whose birthday is today)

1171
00:42:14,300 --> 00:42:17,366
(Unaware of anything,
HANBI is monitoring stage rehearsal)

1172
00:42:17,866 --> 00:42:21,233
(Heading towards HANBI with a birthday cake)

1173
00:42:21,728 --> 00:42:25,800
(Delivering fake announcements
to catch HANBI's attention)

1174
00:42:26,033 --> 00:42:27,232
(Focused)

1175
00:42:27,232 --> 00:42:28,087
HANBI: Yes, yes.

1176
00:42:28,448 --> 00:42:30,528
DANIEL: Five, six, seven, eight!

1177
00:42:30,656 --> 00:42:31,712
HANBI: Happy birthday to you.

1178
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,696
DANIEL: Five, six, seven, eight!

1179
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,808
(The surprise birthday party)
ALL: Happy birthday to you.

1180
00:42:35,808 --> 00:42:36,736
(For HANBI, started by DANIEL's lead)

1181
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:40,466
ALL: Happy birthday to you.

1182
00:42:40,466 --> 00:42:46,100
ALL: Happy birthday to our dear HANBI.
Happy birthday to you!

1183
00:42:49,043 --> 00:42:50,112
TRAINEE: HANBI!

1184
00:42:50,112 --> 00:42:51,733
HANBI: Thank you.

1185
00:42:52,288 --> 00:42:54,259
TRAINEE: HANBI, HANBI!

1186
00:42:54,323 --> 00:42:56,928
HANBI: Thank you!

1187
00:42:57,024 --> 00:42:58,266
HANBI: Thank you so much.

1188
00:42:58,266 --> 00:43:00,066
(First, make a wish)
HANBI: I should make a wish first, right?

1189
00:43:00,333 --> 00:43:01,800
HANBI: A man holding flowers.

1190
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,500
HANBI: Please remember Five Boys Over Flowers.

1191
00:43:03,766 --> 00:43:04,966
(A quick promo moment)

1192
00:43:05,700 --> 00:43:07,566
(After making a heartfelt wish, blowing out the candle)

1193
00:43:08,544 --> 00:43:11,008
(Happiness doubles when shared)

1194
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:12,512
DANIEL: HANBI, there's one more gift.

1195
00:43:12,512 --> 00:43:13,088
HANBI: What is it?

1196
00:43:13,300 --> 00:43:15,933
SONGHA: HANBI's been
using the same wallet for a long time.

1197
00:43:15,933 --> 00:43:16,768
HANBI: Oh, that's true!

1198
00:43:16,838 --> 00:43:19,808
SONGHA: So we wanted to get you a new one.

1199
00:43:20,133 --> 00:43:22,033
(A wallet gift for HANBI)

1200
00:43:22,033 --> 00:43:24,533
HANBI: What is it, what is it?

1201
00:43:24,533 --> 00:43:25,120
DANIEL: Do you recognize it?

1202
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:25,666
TATA: Do you know it?

1203
00:43:25,666 --> 00:43:28,200
(Remembered the wallet HANBI was fond of)
HANBI: Isn't this the one I mentioned before?

1204
00:43:29,184 --> 00:43:31,392
(Touched by their thoughtfulness)
HANBI: Thank you so much.

1205
00:43:32,768 --> 00:43:35,936
HANBI: My favorite item has changed.
It used to be my monitor, now it's this wallet.

1206
00:43:35,936 --> 00:43:38,880
(Favorite item changed to the wallet)

1207
00:43:39,552 --> 00:43:41,184
(The party ends with another round of thanks)
HANBI: Wow, it's nice.

1208
00:43:41,184 --> 00:43:43,232
HANBI: I'll carry it well, thank you so much.

1209
00:43:43,379 --> 00:43:44,512
(PM 5:30)
TRAINEE: Let's head to the field.

1210
00:43:44,512 --> 00:43:45,440
(Camera rehearsal)
TRAINEE: Let's go.

1211
00:43:45,664 --> 00:43:46,560
- TRAINEE: Thank you.
- TRAINEE: Let's go.

1212
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:47,360
HANBI: Let's go to the stage.

1213
00:43:48,896 --> 00:43:51,500
(The trainees prepare for the camera rehearsal)

1214
00:43:52,033 --> 00:43:54,366
(But)

1215
00:43:55,456 --> 00:43:58,304
(The STAFF suddenly call an emergency meeting)

1216
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:01,728
STAFF: Oh, is it raining?

1217
00:44:02,633 --> 00:44:05,166
(Is it raining...?)

1218
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:07,733
(While celebrating HANBI's birthday,)

1219
00:44:08,384 --> 00:44:11,040
(Dark clouds roll in)

1220
00:44:11,733 --> 00:44:14,266
(And then it starts to rain)

1221
00:44:14,533 --> 00:44:17,000
(The clear weather)

1222
00:44:17,666 --> 00:44:21,133
(Suddenly changes unexpectedly)

1223
00:44:21,633 --> 00:44:27,300
(The STAFF scramble at the sudden rain)

1224
00:44:28,633 --> 00:44:32,992
STAFF: Since it's raining, please get ready
and wait in the waiting room.

1225
00:44:32,992 --> 00:44:34,176
ALL: Yes.

1226
00:44:34,321 --> 00:44:35,456
JUSTIN: No!

1227
00:44:36,732 --> 00:44:38,336
HANBI: Why is it raining...

1228
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:41,133
DANIEL: It's raining quite a bit, isn't it?

1229
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:42,688
HANBI: Yeah, it really is.

1230
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:47,800
(Raindrops getting thicker)

1231
00:44:48,966 --> 00:44:52,866
(Even pooling water on the stage floor)

1232
00:44:53,024 --> 00:44:55,520
(STAFF step in to manage the situation)
STAFF: We'll sort out the situation now.

1233
00:44:55,584 --> 00:44:56,448
ALL: Yes.

1234
00:44:56,512 --> 00:44:59,616
(According to the forecast, the rain should stop at 6:30)
STAFF: We expect it to stop around 6:30.

1235
00:44:59,616 --> 00:45:00,256
TRAINEE: Yes.

1236
00:45:00,256 --> 00:45:03,008
(For now, all schedules are delayed until then)
STAFF: At 6:30, change outfits

1237
00:45:03,008 --> 00:45:06,304
- STAFF: and proceed with the camera rehearsal.
- ALL: Yes.

1238
00:45:06,336 --> 00:45:10,592
STAFF: If it's still raining and the stage is slippery,

1239
00:45:10,592 --> 00:45:14,144
STAFF: we'll cancel today's rehearsal.

1240
00:45:14,592 --> 00:45:16,288
(Camera rehearsal)

1241
00:45:16,288 --> 00:45:20,480
(A full run-through before filming to check
camera angles, movement, and timing)

1242
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:26,400
(They may have to go straight
to the real stage without rehearsal)

1243
00:45:26,833 --> 00:45:32,400
(For students with no broadcast experience,
it's practically a gamble)

1244
00:45:33,033 --> 00:45:39,400
(Up to the camera rehearsal)

1245
00:45:40,320 --> 00:45:41,568
TRAINEE: Has the rain stopped?

1246
00:45:41,568 --> 00:45:43,552
(The rain gets heavier as time passes)
TRAINEE: It feels like it slowed a bit.

1247
00:45:46,494 --> 00:45:47,936
WOOLIN: Wow, it's raining a lot?

1248
00:45:47,936 --> 00:45:48,576
KASSHO: Exactly.

1249
00:45:48,766 --> 00:45:50,066
TATA: Is it raining?

1250
00:45:50,300 --> 00:45:51,333
NICHOLAS: TATA, look.

1251
00:45:51,333 --> 00:45:52,800
JUSTIN: It's raining a lot.

1252
00:45:53,594 --> 00:45:54,816
TATA: Huh???

1253
00:45:55,648 --> 00:45:59,232
(The changing schedule is shared with the trainees)
STAFF: Let me update you.

1254
00:45:59,808 --> 00:46:04,433
(Rain is now forecast until 9)
STAFF: It's now postponed to rain until 9 o'clock.

1255
00:46:04,433 --> 00:46:05,920
(They decide to wait until 7 o'clock)
STAFF: We'll monitor the situation until 7 o'clock.

1256
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:06,816
NICHOLAS: Okay.

1257
00:46:08,256 --> 00:46:12,133
(Current time PM 6:30)

1258
00:46:12,133 --> 00:46:14,600
(They should be doing the camera rehearsal
according to schedule)

1259
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:17,833
(Assessing the situation, HARUTA goes outside to check)

1260
00:46:18,144 --> 00:46:19,933
HARUTA: It's raining more than I thought.

1261
00:46:20,544 --> 00:46:22,240
(Current time PM 7:00)

1262
00:46:23,027 --> 00:46:24,608
HARUTA: I didn't know it would rain like this.

1263
00:46:25,733 --> 00:46:28,233
(HANBI also joins)

1264
00:46:28,448 --> 00:46:29,760
(More rain than expected)
HARUTA: It's raining more than expected.

1265
00:46:29,760 --> 00:46:30,752
HANBI: It's raining a lot.

1266
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:33,696
HANBI: Even though I like rain, this is too much.

1267
00:46:33,696 --> 00:46:35,616
HARUTA: The weather is always bad.

1268
00:46:36,147 --> 00:46:37,824
HARUTA: But it was nice this morning.

1269
00:46:37,824 --> 00:46:39,808
HANBI: Yeah, the weather was really clear this morning.

1270
00:46:40,230 --> 00:46:41,696
HANBI: Who would've thought it would suddenly rain?

1271
00:46:42,592 --> 00:46:43,520
HARUTA: I can't see when it'll stop.

1272
00:46:43,520 --> 00:46:44,736
HANBI: It shows no sign of stopping.

1273
00:46:45,651 --> 00:46:46,560
HARUTA: But!

1274
00:46:46,784 --> 00:46:48,352
HARUTA: We'll do well tomorrow.

1275
00:46:48,352 --> 00:46:49,664
HANBI: Oh, confidence.

1276
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:50,688
HARUTA: We have to do well.

1277
00:46:50,688 --> 00:46:51,904
HANBI: We definitely have to do well tomorrow.

1278
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:55,100
(They desperately hope the rain stops)
HANBI: I wish the rain would stop.

1279
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:55,936
HARUTA: I want to get on stage soon.

1280
00:46:55,936 --> 00:46:56,736
HANBI: Right.

1281
00:46:56,736 --> 00:46:57,664
HARUTA: I'm excited.

1282
00:46:58,233 --> 00:47:01,900
(Instinctively doing choreography)

1283
00:47:02,900 --> 00:47:05,400
(As if sensing their eagerness,
the rain begins to ease)

1284
00:47:06,333 --> 00:47:09,066
(Finally, the rain has stopped)

1285
00:47:09,966 --> 00:47:14,633
(They remove all the water from the stage for safety)

1286
00:47:14,784 --> 00:47:16,500
HYUNJUN: The rain has stopped!

1287
00:47:16,768 --> 00:47:18,336
(The good news reaches the trainees)
TRAINEE: The rain has stopped.

1288
00:47:19,666 --> 00:47:22,900
(They finally prepare for the camera rehearsal)

1289
00:47:23,744 --> 00:47:24,608
(PM 9:00)
TRAINEE: Let's go, let's go!

1290
00:47:25,888 --> 00:47:27,840
TATA: Nervous, so nervous.

1291
00:47:28,736 --> 00:47:30,592
(After about four hours of waiting)
HAMIN: Let's go!

1292
00:47:31,424 --> 00:47:33,408
(Finally heading out for camera rehearsal)
KASSHO: Let's go.

1293
00:47:35,233 --> 00:47:37,600
(The weather turns chilly after the rain)

1294
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:39,904
(The current perceived temperature is...)

1295
00:47:40,128 --> 00:47:42,688
TRAINEE: Cold! Cold!

1296
00:47:43,233 --> 00:47:45,344
(Even the lighting looks like a Siberian freezer)

1297
00:47:45,856 --> 00:47:47,072
(The blue lighting reminds them of someone)

1298
00:47:47,072 --> 00:47:48,288
TRAINEE: MINYEONG!

1299
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:51,900
(MINYEONG has "ascended")
TRAINEE: MINYEONG!

1300
00:47:51,900 --> 00:47:53,472
TRAINEE: MINYEONG!

1301
00:47:53,472 --> 00:47:54,400
TRAINEE: So cold!

1302
00:47:55,100 --> 00:47:57,266
HANBI: It's okay. Once we dance, we'll warm up.

1303
00:47:57,472 --> 00:47:59,500
(Before the camera rehearsal)
HYUNJUN: Well, just...

1304
00:47:59,552 --> 00:48:01,000
(STAFF announcement)
HYUNJUN: They said don't dance too hard.

1305
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:01,866
HYUNJUN: If the stage is slippery,
tell them right away!

1306
00:48:01,866 --> 00:48:02,900
HYUNJUN: They said not to dance too hard.

1307
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:04,384
(Stage check is the priority for safety)

1308
00:48:04,384 --> 00:48:05,312
JUSTIN: It's fine though?

1309
00:48:06,182 --> 00:48:06,752
HANBI: Seems fine.

1310
00:48:06,752 --> 00:48:07,392
JUSTIN: It's fine.

1311
00:48:07,392 --> 00:48:08,928
HANBI: It's actually better because it's less slippery.

1312
00:48:09,056 --> 00:48:10,866
NICHOLAS: Maybe it depends on the shoes?

1313
00:48:11,038 --> 00:48:12,608
SONGHA: It probably depends on the shoes.

1314
00:48:13,100 --> 00:48:15,552
STAFF: We'll begin the camera rehearsal.

1315
00:48:15,648 --> 00:48:16,466
ALL: Yes!

1316
00:48:16,736 --> 00:48:19,072
(First, a stage check)
STAFF: Everyone, standby. Two, one, go!

1317
00:48:20,166 --> 00:48:23,533
(Into The New World)

1318
00:48:24,566 --> 00:48:26,466
(They run it like a real performance)

1319
00:48:27,300 --> 00:48:28,666
(With full outfits and everything prepared)

1320
00:48:29,633 --> 00:48:31,233
(As if it's the real performance)

1321
00:48:31,433 --> 00:48:33,200
(The problem is...)

1322
00:48:35,100 --> 00:48:36,866
(Even after wiping, the stage is still slippery)

1323
00:48:37,136 --> 00:48:38,272
DANIEL: Don't go forward!

1324
00:48:39,100 --> 00:48:40,666
(Right as he says that...)

1325
00:48:41,033 --> 00:48:43,200
(People start slipping everywhere)

1326
00:48:43,552 --> 00:48:44,288
(TATA coming to take care of his older member)

1327
00:48:44,288 --> 00:48:45,472
TATA: See?

1328
00:48:46,272 --> 00:48:48,416
(Camera rehearsal stops)

1329
00:48:48,659 --> 00:48:49,504
TRAINEE: Oh, no...

1330
00:48:49,632 --> 00:48:52,448
(HANBI, JUSTIN...)
TRAINEE: Who said it wasn't slippery?

1331
00:48:52,544 --> 00:48:54,500
(HANBI is checking if everyone is okay)
HANBI: Are you okay?

1332
00:48:54,500 --> 00:48:56,000
HYUNJUN: Pain is youth!

1333
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:57,216
(If you're hurt, let's go to the hospital)
HANBI: This spot is really...

1334
00:48:58,176 --> 00:49:00,096
HANBI: I think this white part is the problem.

1335
00:49:00,448 --> 00:49:02,752
(The stage looks frosted)
HANBI: It's like dew.

1336
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:05,280
(River located right next to the school)

1337
00:49:06,368 --> 00:49:08,704
(After the rain, the school is in thick fog)

1338
00:49:09,664 --> 00:49:13,216
DANIEL: Let's bring some towels and wipe it together.

1339
00:49:13,216 --> 00:49:16,864
DANIEL: If 15 of us wipe it together,
it will be done quickly!

1340
00:49:16,864 --> 00:49:20,256
HANBI: If all 15 of us clean together, it'll be fast.

1341
00:49:20,433 --> 00:49:22,833
HANBI: Everyone, grab towels!

1342
00:49:23,104 --> 00:49:25,966
(While the STAFF devises stage countermeasures)
TRAINEE: It's very slippery here.

1343
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:29,280
(A bunch of "foot-powered cleaners" appear)

1344
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:32,766
(Among them, the pink version is exceptionally good)

1345
00:49:32,806 --> 00:49:33,760
TRAINEE: Hey, Cinderella!

1346
00:49:34,433 --> 00:49:37,766
(It's HYUNJUN)

1347
00:49:38,100 --> 00:49:40,128
(Found a new talent)
TRAINEE: HYUNJUN!

1348
00:49:40,192 --> 00:49:42,266
(No one can keep up)
NICHOLAS: HYUNJUN!

1349
00:49:42,272 --> 00:49:45,120
HANBI: HYUNJUN, you need to clean
there quickly. What are you doing?

1350
00:49:46,176 --> 00:49:47,712
SONGHA: Our Snow White!

1351
00:49:47,910 --> 00:49:49,500
(It's Cinderella?)
HYUNJUN: It's Cinderella, Cinderella.

1352
00:49:49,500 --> 00:49:50,944
(Got teased by his seniors)
SONGHA: Cinderella, sorry.

1353
00:49:50,944 --> 00:49:52,384
NICHOLAS: Hey, Cinderella, here!

1354
00:49:52,566 --> 00:49:55,833
(STAFF also join Cinderella)
TRAINEE: Cinderella is young.

1355
00:49:56,400 --> 00:49:59,232
(They scrub hard with all their strength)

1356
00:49:59,232 --> 00:50:00,736
SONGHA: Why does it feel the same even after cleaning?

1357
00:50:00,736 --> 00:50:01,632
HYUNJUN: No, it's not.

1358
00:50:01,632 --> 00:50:02,752
SONGHA: Is it not? Is it just my imagination?

1359
00:50:02,816 --> 00:50:05,376
HANBI: No, it keeps coming back
no matter how much we clean.

1360
00:50:05,376 --> 00:50:07,520
HANBI: Clean it once, and then clean it again.

1361
00:50:07,733 --> 00:50:09,408
(If you wipe like grilling meat)
HANBI: Keep wiping and...

1362
